---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { LINKEDIN_URL, GITHUB_URL, EMAIL } from '../consts';
---

<Layout 
	title="About Gregory Wainer"
	description="Masters Electrical Engineer at Virginia Tech focusing on RF systems. Recent BS Computer Science graduate (2025) with expertise in autonomous systems and satellite communications."
>
	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8 text-black">About Me</h1>
		
		<div class="prose-content text-gray-700 space-y-6 mb-12">
			<p class="text-xl leading-relaxed">
				I'm Gregory Wainer, a Masters Electrical Engineer at Virginia Tech with a focus on RF systems. 
				Recent BS Computer Science graduate (2025) with expertise spanning autonomous systems, satellite communications, embedded systems, and advanced rocketry applications.
			</p>
			
			<p>
				Currently, I'm working as a Mission Systems Division Intern at the Hume Center for National Security and Technology, 
				where I'm contributing to the finalization of <strong>UtProSat</strong>, a cube satellite that will deploy on 
				Blue Origin's New Glenn 2nd Launch. My responsibilities include implementing communication between ground stations 
				and payload systems, developing experiment scheduling algorithms, and creating robust system recovery mechanisms.
			</p>
			
			<p>
				As the 2025 Payload and Telemetry Lead for Rocketry at Virginia Tech, I've designed and implemented sophisticated 
				telemetry systems including LoRa mesh networks with Listen Before Talk protocols, multi-platform applications 
				spanning iOS (Swift) and embedded systems (Rust/C++), and active drag control systems for precision altitude management.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Education -->
		<section class="mb-12">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Education</h2>
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="border border-gray-200 p-6">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Master of Science - Electrical Engineering</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Virginia Tech | August 2025 - May 2027</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700">Focus: RF systems and communications</p>
				</div>
				<div class="border border-gray-200 p-6">
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Bachelor of Science - Computer Science</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-600 mb-2">Virginia Tech | August 2022 - May 2025</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700">Strong foundation in software engineering and systems programming</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Key Experience -->
		<section class="mb-12">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Key Experience</h2>
			<div class="space-y-8">
				<div>
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Autonomous Systems Research</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
						Led the development of V2V GPS-denied unmanned autonomous vehicles for RTX's Autonomous Vehicle Competition, 
						where we placed <strong>2nd overall</strong> with the fastest and most accurate system. I integrated 
						Visual-Inertial-Odometry systems (OpenVINS) into PX4 and successfully migrated codebases from ROS1 to ROS2.
					</p>
				</div>
				
				<div>
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Naval Systems Development</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
						At Naval Surface Warfare Center Carderock Division, I contributed to next-generation autonomous systems 
						for Unmanned Surface Vessels using Agile methodologies. I worked extensively with NEMA 2000 CAN systems 
						and Parker PLCs for vehicle control and system communication.
					</p>
				</div>
				
				<div>
					<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Embedded Systems Development</h3>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
						Developed comprehensive device drivers in C and Rust for various sensors and actuators including 
						PWM servos, IMUs, UBLOX GPS modules, barometers, and SPI flash chips, primarily targeting RP2040 microcontrollers. 
						Currently developing Kalman filters for improved sensor fusion and data accuracy.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Technical Expertise -->
		<section class="mb-12">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Technical Expertise</h2>
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
				<div>
					<h4 class="font-bold mb-3 text-black">Languages</h4>
					<ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-1 text-sm">
						<li>• C/C++</li>
						<li>• Rust</li>
						<li>• Python</li>
						<li>• Swift</li>
						<li>• TypeScript</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="font-bold mb-3 text-black">Frameworks</h4>
					<ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-1 text-sm">
						<li>• PX4/ArduPilot</li>
						<li>• ROS/ROS2</li>
						<li>• OpenCV</li>
						<li>• Astro</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="font-bold mb-3 text-black">Hardware</h4>
					<ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-1 text-sm">
						<li>• RP2040</li>
						<li>• ARM Cortex</li>
						<li>• GNSS/GPS</li>
						<li>• LoRa Radios</li>
						<li>• IMU Sensors</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="font-bold mb-3 text-black">Protocols</h4>
					<ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-1 text-sm">
						<li>• CAN Bus</li>
						<li>• NEMA 2000</li>
						<li>• I2C/SPI</li>
						<li>• Bluetooth</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Certifications -->
		<section class="mb-12">
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Certifications</h2>
			<div class="border border-gray-200 p-6">
				<h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">FAA Part 107</h3>
				<p class="text-gray-700">Remote Pilot Certificate for commercial drone operations</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- Contact -->
		<section>
			<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-black">Get In Touch</h2>
			<p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
				I'm always interested in discussing autonomous systems, embedded engineering, space technology, 
				and innovative engineering challenges. Feel free to reach out!
			</p>
			<div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
				<a 
					href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}
					class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 border border-black text-black hover:bg-black hover:text-white transition-colors"
				>
					<svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
						<path d="M2.003 5.884L10 9.882l7.997-3.998A2 2 0 0016 4H4a2 2 0 00-1.997 1.884z"/>
						<path d="M18 8.118l-8 4-8-4V14a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8.118z"/>
					</svg>
					Email Me
				</a>
				<a 
					href={LINKEDIN_URL}
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
					class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-black hover:text-gray-700 transition-colors border border-gray-300 hover:border-gray-400"
				>
					<svg class="w-5 h-5 mr-2" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
